Executive Profile
Stephen C. Curley J.D.Member, Mintz, Levin, Cohn, Ferris, Glovsky and Popeo, P.C.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 1 different industries.See Board Relationships----
Background

		Mr. Stephen C. Curley, also known as Steve, is a Member at Mintz, Levin, Cohn, Ferris, Glovsky and Popeo, P.C. He also serves as Co-chair of the firm’s Healthcare Deal Lawyers working group. At the firm, his practice areas include tax, corporate & securities, health law, international, and mintz levin center for health law & policy. Mr. Curley’s industry coverage at the firm includes financial services, health care, life sciences, manufacturing, nonprofits, real estate, ... retail & consumer products, and technology. Mr. Curley has acted as a Principal Tax Counsel for many domestic and foreign investors in connection with their corporate direct investment and mergers and acquisitions activities in the United States and their investments in United States real estate. He was employed at Hogan & Hartson L.L.P. Earlier, Mr. Curley was a Founding Partner of Haythe & Curley. He was a Presiding Partner at another international law firm and before that, was a Managing Partner of a prominent international boutique, which he co-founded. He is a Director at HealthpointCapital, LLC. Mr. Curley serves on the Board of a major youth services organization in New York City. He has served as a Director at numerous charitable and civic groups. For more than 30 years, he has advised United States and foreign companies on transactional matters, including corporate mergers and acquisitions, debt and equity financings, infrastructure projects, and related tax issues. A significant part of his practice has involved advising clients on matters related to international investment and transactional matters. This includes experience working with Chinese clients and advising international clients regarding their investments and operations in China. His private equity practice includes representation of sponsors in fund formation and the funds themselves in their investment activities. He has also represented both companies and individuals involved in tax controversies and disputes with the IRS. For many years, he has advised clients in many segments of the healthcare industry in connection with transactional matters. Internationally, Mr. Curley has been involved with numerous joint ventures, acquisitions, and financings in many industries including energy, retail distribution, media, real estate, healthcare, shipping, finance, and apparel. Mr. Curley has broad and varied corporate, tax, and healthcare experience.  He has been awarded New York Super Lawyers: Tax (2007, 2009 – 2012) and Martindale-Hubbell AV Preeminent. Mr. Curley is admitted to practice in New York and Pennsylvania. While in law school, he served as Articles Editor for The University of Chicago Law Review. Mr. Curley received a B.A. from Haverford College, a J.D. from the University of Chicago Law School and an L.L.M. in Taxation from New York University Law School.Read Full Background




